- The student ID is assumed to be a unique identifier for each student in the database; 
- The device name, condition name, and skill name are used to provide context to the performance metrics; 
- A higher rating generally indicates better performance; 
- A lower error count generally indicates better performance.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT user_name
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT student_id FROM performances);
